{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"],"generated":true,"title":"Composing Large Games","anchor":"Composing-Large-Games"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers."}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Gnusto game is one type conforming to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". That does "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" mean it must live in one file. A large game splits cleanly along two of its three parts today; the third has a known boundary worth understanding."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The one rule: declarations stay in the struct body","anchor":"The-one-rule-declarations-stay-in-the-struct-body","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Locations, items, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state are "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"stored properties"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and Swift requires stored properties to be declared in a type’s main body — not in an extension. The bootstrap also discovers every entity by reflecting over the single "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type and naming each entity after its property ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"let foyer = Location { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" becomes "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"foyer\""},{"type":"text","text":"). So all entity declarations live together, in the file that declares the struct:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct OperaHouse: Game {","    let foyer = Location { name(\"Foyer of the Opera House\"); … }","    let bar   = Location { name(\"Foyer Bar\"); dark }","    let cloak = Item { name(\"velvet cloak\"); wearable }","    @Global var disturbances = 0","    \/\/ …","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(If you reach the point where even the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declarations"}]},{"type":"text","text":" need to span files or ship in a separate package, reach for "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"content bundles"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — a region declared as its own "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"type":"text","text":" type. See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles"},{"type":"text","text":".)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"`map` and `rules` compose across files","anchor":"map-and-rules-compose-across-files","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" are result-builder properties, and the builder accepts whole "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules"},{"type":"text","text":" values as well as individual entries. That means you can break each one into per-region helper properties and splice them together:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension OperaHouse {","    var map: WorldMap {","        foyerMap        \/\/ a WorldMap, defined elsewhere","        cloakroomMap","        barMap","        player.starts(in: foyer)","    }","","    var rules: Rules {","        foyerRules      \/\/ a Rules value, defined elsewhere","        cloakroomRules","        barRules","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each helper is itself a builder property, annotated so its body can use the block syntax. Put each region in its own file:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ OperaHouse+Bar.swift","extension OperaHouse {","    @MapBuilder var barMap: WorldMap {","        bar.north(foyer)","        message.starts(in: bar)","    }","","    @RuleBuilder var barRules: Rules {","        bar.beforeEachTurn { … }","        bar.afterEachTurn  { … }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inside an extension, the bare identifiers ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bar"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"message"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"player"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"command"},{"type":"text","text":", your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":"s) resolve to the same declarations and engine globals they would inside the struct — nothing needs to be passed around."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"A recommended layout for a large game","anchor":"A-recommended-layout-for-a-large-game","level":2},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["MyGame\/","  MyGame.swift            \/\/ struct: all Location\/Item\/@Global declarations,","                          \/\/   plus map { … } and rules { … } that compose the regions","  MyGame+Foyer.swift      \/\/ foyerMap  + foyerRules","  MyGame+Cloakroom.swift  \/\/ cloakroomMap + cloakroomRules","  MyGame+Bar.swift        \/\/ barMap    + barRules"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The struct file stays a readable table of contents — what exists and how the regions connect — while each region’s geography and logic lives next to itself."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Worked example","anchor":"Worked-example","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/SplitGame\/"},{"type":"text","text":" is a minimal game authored exactly this way: declarations in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SplitGame.swift"},{"type":"text","text":", with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gardenMap"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gardenRules"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SplitGame+Garden.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"houseMap"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"houseRules"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SplitGame+House.swift"},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MultiFileCompositionTests"},{"type":"text","text":" boots it and confirms that the map entries and rules from every file take effect at runtime."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"What splits, and how","anchor":"What-splits-and-how","level":2},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Part"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Splits across files?"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — compose from per-region "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" helpers."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — compose from per-region "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" helpers."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom verbs"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — a game’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" block, and any bundle’s."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Entity declarations"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the struct body by default; across types\/packages via "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The table above is the extension-based split: one "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game"},{"type":"text","text":" struct, declarations in its body, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" composed from per-region helpers. When a region needs to own its "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declarations"}]},{"type":"text","text":" too — or ship as a package — promote it to a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}]},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/EntityID":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"EntityID","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EntityID"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A stable, human-readable entity name derived from the Swift property label"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at registration time ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"let bar = Location { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" → "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntityID(\"bar\")"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/entityid","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EntityID"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}],"title":"Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContents","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected content bundles a game declares, in declaration order."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontents","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Game":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Game","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Game"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A complete game: declarations, geography, and rules."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/game","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Game"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/WorldMap":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"WorldMap","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"WorldMap"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The geography and initial placements of a game, declared in one block:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/worldmap","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"WorldMap"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Rules":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Rules","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Rules"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected rules of a game, declared in one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" block. Large games"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compose: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var rules: Rules { cloakRules; barRules }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/rules","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Rules"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GamePlugin","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"importable unit of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}]},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Plugins":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Plugins","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContent":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContent","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Content Bundles","abstract":[{"text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles"}}}